        </p>
        <a name="works"></a> 
        <h2>How the site works</h2>
        <p>
            When you first sign up we attempt to verify your identity, and find you on the electoral role. 
            If we find you then you become a verified user, and your votes count towards the national 
            statistics that compare the way the public have votes to the way the MPs have voted. 
        </p>
        <p>
            If we are unable to verify your identity, then you can sill use all the features of the 
            site, but your votes only count towards an opinion poll. 
        </p>
        <p>
            Regardless of whether or not you are a verified user, you can participate in the people’s debates, 
            and view the parliamentary and media debates. 
        </p>
